  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Teacher",
  "description": "<h1><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></h1><p><strong>Instruction & Delivery:</strong> Deliver engaging, clear, and effective lessons to students with diverse learning styles and abilities. Mainly from K2 to P4 English and Math.</p><p><strong>Classroom Management:</strong> Establish and maintain a positive, safe, and productive learning environment. Enforce school rules and behavioral expectations.</p><p><strong>Assessment & Grading:</strong> Create quizzes, tests, projects, and exams. Evaluate student work, provide meaningful feedback, paper marking and assign grades.</p><p><strong>Communication: </strong>Keep supervisor update about student learning progress.</p><p><strong>Administrative Tasks:</strong> Complete necessary paperwork, including attendance records, feedback records, exam records.<br /></p><h1><strong>Requirements</strong></h1><ul><li>Minimum Secondary 3 education.</li><li>Pleasant disposition with good communication skills.</li><li>Enjoy working with children ranging from 7 - 12 years of age.</li><li>Capable of communicating in simple Chinese.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Attitude & Personality & Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Enjoys interacting with children</li><li>Stable, reliable, and able to commit for at least 3 months</li><li>Open to learning and participating in teaching development</li><li>Responsible, diligent, and not performative or careless</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Workplace details</strong><br />Location: 519 BALESTIER ROAD, #02-05, LE SHANTIER, SINGAPORE 329852<br />Working hour: 9am-6pm or 10am-7pm<br /></p>",
